%Steps%

During this step, we're going to put together a state machine that will take advantage of our newly made variables.

1.	Double-click on **AnimGraph** in the **My Blueprint** tab to open it.

	![](AnimGraph.png)

1.	Right-click the graph and select **State Machines > Add New State Machine... ** in the **Context Menu**.

	![](AddNewSM.png)

1.	Right-click on **New State Machine** in the **My Blueprint** tab and name it "Arms State Machine".

	![](NewArmsStateMachine.png)

1.	Connect the ouput execution pin on the "Arms State Machine" node to the **Result** input execution pin on the **Final Animation Pose** node.

	![](ConnectedArmsStateMachine.png)

1.	Double-click the "Arms State Machine" node to open its graph for editing.

